The Flower Protocol

Think of the web as an ecosystem.

Trees

* Mature authoritative topics.
* Hard to replace.

Flowers

* Emerging questions.
* Small niches.
* Local opportunities.
* New terminology.
* Long-tail searches.

Vines

* Topics connecting multiple domains.

Dead Wood

* Outdated content.
* Broken links.
* Abandoned ideas.

Pollinators

* People.
* Search engines.
* AI systems.
* Social sharing.

Pantheon shouldn’t be trying to become the biggest tree.

It should become the best pollinator.

